This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of 2D bounding box car detection. It also involves the use of neural networks for detection, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it aims to bridge the reality gap between synthetic and real data, which is a common problem in robotics. 

Machine learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves training a neural network on synthetic data. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of synthetic data to improve the performance of a neural network. 

Finally, the paper may also belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it involves the use of structured domain randomization to improve the security of the neural network against adversarial attacks.
